            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I had the same issue when installing the LSP with Nix.\n\nPasting my solution in case it can help others:\n\n```nix\n  # Nix (home-manager)\n  programs.neovim = {\n    extraPackages = with pkgs; [\n      astro-language-server\n    ];\n    initLua = ''\n      # passing the current typescript package's sdk path to neovim,\n      # don't know if this is the most elegant way to do it, yet it works\n      vim.g.tsdk = \"${pkgs.typescript}/lib/node_modules/typescript/lib\"\n      \n      vim.cmd.source(\"${config.home.homeDirectory}/.dotfiles/nvim/init.lua\")\n    '';\n  };\n```\n\n```lua\n-- Nvim's lspconfig\n\n    vim.lsp.config['astro'] = {\n      init_options = {\n        typescript = {\n          tsdk = vim.g.tsdk,\n        },\n      },\n    }\n\n    vim.lsp.enable('astro')\n```",
